OL,4,CFrom Afghan interpreter to US homeless
OL,5,C- until reaching the American dream
OL,6, Zia Ghafoori, his pregnant wife and
OL,7, their three small children landed in
OL,8, the United States from their home in
OL,9, Kabul in September 2014.
OL,11,FHe held five US visas - a reward for 14
OL,12,Fyears of service as an interpreter with
OL,13,FUS Special Forces in Afghanistan.
OL,15,FBut the benefits stopped there. Upon
OL,16,Farrival, Zia found himself homeless -
OL,17,Fsent to a shelter by a well-meaning
OL,18,Fvolunteer who told him it would be a
OL,19,Fplace for him and his family to start a
OL,20,Fnew life.
